<TITLE> Mymensingh court jails 15 for abetting militancy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Mymensingh, July 29 (bdnews24.com) -- A Mymensingh court Sunday sentenced 15 members with ties to the banned militant outfit JMB to 10 years in jail for sheltering Siddiqul Islam, popularly known as Bangla Bhai, and abetting militancy. Magistrate Shefali Begum of the Speedy Trial Court handed down the verdict. The convicts have to pay Tk 10,000 each in fine or serve out 10 more months in jail if they fail to pay the sum. The convicts are Dr Shamsul Haque (age unknown), Mukhles, 37, Abdur Rahman, 32, Mannan, 26, Nazmul Haque, 30, Abdul Hye, 50, Mohammad Ali Master, 60, Shahidullah Hattu, 35, Saheb Ali Master, 37, Fulbar Hossain, 35, Sekandar Ali, 26, Hatem Ali, 18, Abul, 35, Motaleb known as Hira Khalifa, 45. They are all residents of Muktagachha upazila in the district. RAB arrested the convicts in a predawn raid on Ichhakhali Bazaar while having a secret meeting on May 6. The RAB arrested JMB second in command Bangla Bhai in Rampur village of the upazila on March 6, 2006. He was hanged for his role in the killings of two judges in the southern district of Jhalakathi. bdnews2
